parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not provided with the necessary protection.
symptoms: The airbag does not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadvertent deployment of the airbag can cause unexpected injuries or distractions while driving, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The airbag deploys unexpectedly
without a crash or impact
causing injuries or distractions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor or system can prevent the airbag from deploying in a crash, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on
the airbag sensor is disconnected
or the airbag system fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deployment of the airbag can cause injuries, such as broken bones or bruising, even when the occupants are wearing seatbelts.
symptoms: Injuries
such as broken bones or bruising
occur due to the deployment of the airbag.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or shift into improper gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls when taking off
has difficulty shifting into gears
makes a loud noise
has a sudden loss of power
the transmission hunts for gears
the transmission fails to engage
the vehicle shifts into neutral or reverse unexpectedly
the transmission overheats
the vehicle has acceleration failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TCU can cause the transmission to shift into improper gears, leading to loss of power, stalling, or accidents.
symptoms: The transmission shifts into neutral or reverse unexpectedly
the transmission fails to engage
the vehicle has acceleration failure
the transmission hunts for gears
the D4 light comes on and stays on
the transmission produces non-existent codes when put into diagnostic mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the axle shaft seal can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The axle shaft seal pops out while driving
the axle boots are dry rotted
cracking
and leaking grease
the vehicle has a sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shift cable can cause the transmission to lock in park position, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shifts into park or reverse unexpectedly
the transmission fails to engage
the vehicle has difficulty shifting into gears
the shift cable breaks or fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt latch can cause the seat belt to become unbuckled while driving, leading to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle comes undone while driving
the seat belt does not stay locked when plugged in
the seat belt unlatches on its own
the seat belt gives a false sense of security
the seat belt strap doubles over
making it difficult to buckle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate restraint of the seat belt can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt does not properly restrain the driver or passenger during an accident
the seat belt fails to deploy
the seat belt does not securely hold a child safety seat in place.
